February 1st outfit 
We kicked off the love ❤️ month, my birthday month, just right. My husband planned a dinner date for us at Andiamo Detroit with a Dining In The Dark experience. I do mean literally in the dark. The lights are very dim while your eyes are covered with an eye mask. I was apprehensive initially but I let my guard down and engaged in the dark. I DIDN’T PEEK 🫣 👀 ONE TIME. I stepped out of my “always gotta be in control” comfort zone, let my real hair down (thanks @ms_tierrac 🥰) and thoroughly enjoyed the evening. No phones 📵, no lights 💡… no distractions of any kind. I drank 2 Ameretto Sours to calm my nerves and the night was amazing 😻 to say the least. 

We relied totally on our 👃🏽 smell, taste 👅, hearing 👂🏽 and touch to maneuver around our 3 course dinner. The waiters dinner clues gave us hint as to what we were being served each course. Ray chose blue menu which was ANYTHING seafood 🦞 and I chose red of course which was ANY KIND of meat. Mind you we’re blindfolded the entire time. We talked the entire time, held hands 👐🏽🫶🏽 and created a really dope memory. The food was delicious 😋 and Mike, the owner, made his way to our table to check on us and even gave us his business card inviting us to his restaurant Joe Muer. Great experience and thanks to my stellar man for planning something so fun ♥️♥️♥️

A mothers love for her son is unremarkable‼️ It’s irrefutably a love like no other 💯 There’s not enough words to describe the love I have for you, my ONLY son. It’s not about “favorites” because that’s something I don’t do with my kids. At times, I felt like I couldn’t make it, or life had gotten me down, I’d look at you and suddenly remember why I couldn’t give up. From that sandy brown curly haired kid to a super fine, seemingly handsome 6 foot 6 stellar, extremely intelligent, supafly, young man, D you are truly one of a kind. I love you💛 and you’ll always be My big ole baby‼️ I know you’re an adult and you’re living life on your own terms, I always pray 🙏🏽 and ask God to keep you covered, to keep His protective angels around you, shield you from any hurt, harm or danger. I just love you so much Son 💛💛💛 I hope 🤞🏽 the very best of life overwhelms you with all the happiness your heart can handle. No matter where I am, just know I’ll ALWAYS be here for you. I know you have this thing called life to live, but remember, you have a praying moma and for you, my life, I’ll give. 

Happiest Of Birthdays 🎂 to You, Son💛💛💛

The serious posture he took when he made his vow to her. The love between these two is deep. Not to mention they’re a sexy couple if I do say so myself. They look so good together. I pray 🙏🏽 that God will remain the glue that binds your union together. I bid you both the love and kindness that was displayed Saturday, May 13th, 2023 💯 times more in the years to come. That, “I can’t live without them” kinda love, a Godly🤍🤍🤍 love. It takes two to wed and it’ll take 3 to remain. Keep God first and you’ll be sure to last til’ death do you part. I love y’all deeply.

Day 14 

For the last 7 years we always celebrate our wedding anniversary with other married couples and then we will head out of the country for vacation. Our 22nd Anniversary we had our Annual Adult Field Day and boy did we have a time. 

Like most events I plan, It was very well thought 💭 out and orchestrated. Very intentional and meaningful. I like to be original and this was one for the books. 

We put the fun 🤩 and excitement back in marriage 

So much to reflect on and I’m sooooo grateful for it ALLLLL. 
I waited a year to post this video and as I reflect on the time and fun had, I’m simply humble and grateful to God for allowing us to see our Jordan year of marriage. A lot of marriages didn’t make it. 😢 Our yearly events have helped save many unions. Couples have come to celebrate with us on the brink of divorce and by the time they leave our event, they feel restored.

Reflections of The Randolph’s 
Day15

SHARE THE LOVE 🖤🖤🖤

As of 10/10/20, here you see 323 years of BLACK LOVE in Detroit, Michigan. ONLY IN DETROIT and share the love like they always shine the hate on our city. Nobody does it better‼️

Marriage is not about “marriage goals”, being the best couple, who has the biggest house, or who looks the best on social media. It’s the FIRST institution of family and a God design between two people that glorifies and edifies God. Marriage is a representation of Christ (What God Joins Together) and is a symbol of His designs. 

2020 we planned “Coming From America 🇺🇸 “ (see Day 3) but due to the shut down of the world 🌎 we wasn’t able to complete the renewal of our vows in Cape Town, South Africa 🇿🇦 with our friends and family.

So to commemorate the milestone moment, I gathered 20 couples and planned a Black Love Matters protest in the heart ♥️ of downtown Detroit to let the world 🌎 know we, as a culture and race, know how to love and although black LIVES definitely matters, when BLACK LOVE is in the home, then our BLACK LIVES MATTER ✊🏽 ✊🏾 ✊🏿 because then love is being instilled and we all know that love overcomes hate.

My mind drifted to thinking about past hurts and ALLLLLLL the people I’ve helped but they hurt me when they KNEW my heart meant good for them.
